  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Bernstein, known and beloved by the world as "Lenny," died at 6:15 p.m. in the presence of his son, Alexander, and physician, Kevin M. Cahill, who said the cause of death was complications of progressive lung failure.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   His last conducting appearance was at Tanglewood, Mass., on Aug. 19. He etched other niches in history by composing the indelible "West Side Story" and teaching a generation about classical music via the innovative television series "Omnibus" .
